title: Strömsö
text:
Strömsö is a <a href="Finland">Finnish</a> television program (in <a href="Swedish%20language">Swedish</a>) which premiered in 2002 on <a href="Yle%20Fem">FST</a> and <a href="Yle%20TV1">TV1</a>, hosted by <a href="Matias%20Jungar">Matias Jungar</a> and <a href="Susanna%20Str%C3%B6m-Wilkinson">Susanna Ström-Wilkinson</a>. The show concentrates on various household subjects, such as cooking and gardening. Its fifth season started on January 29, 2006. Since the beginning of 2007 the show is hosted by <a href="Lee%20Esselstr%C3%B6m">Lee Esselström</a> and <a href="Jocke%20Lax">Jocke Lax</a>.
The show is made at Strömsö (from which the show gets its name), a <a href="villa">villa</a> north of the city of <a href="Vaasa">Vaasa</a>. The villa was built in the 1860s and served as the summer residence for a merchant family from Vaasa for about 100 years.
